# Pull Request Convention

## PR Title Format

```
<type>: <description>
```

## PR Body Required Checklist

```markdown
- [ ] Use a meaningful PR title. Include the name of the modified package.
- [ ] Test your changes in your code.
- [ ] Include URLs to test the changes in the PR body.

This pull request:

- [ ] Fixes a bug
- [ ] Implements a new feature
- [ ] Updates documentation or example code
- [ ] Other

## Changes

### Key Changes
1. Change 1
2. Change 2

Test URL:
- <URL 1>
- <URL 2>
```

## Types (Type)

- **feat** - New feature
- **fix** - Bug fix
- **refactor** - Code refactoring (structure improvement without behavior change)
- **test** - Test code addition/modification
- **style** - Code style changes (formatting, semicolons, etc.)
- **docs** - Project documentation (README, comments, etc.)
- **build** - Build system changes (webpack, npm scripts, etc.)
- **ci** - CI/CD configuration changes
- **revert** - Revert changes
- **content** - User-facing content (blog, images, text, etc.)
- **chore** - Other tasks (dependencies, dev environment, etc.)

